reviews.review: This movie is all about damage control, JJ does a great job at attempting to fix Rian Johnson's sabotage in the last Jedi. This movie isn't perfect but he sure gave it hell. Thank you for trying JJ!!

Million times better than 7 and 8. I compare it to Revenge of the sith because not many people liked 1 and 2 but liked therevenge of the sith. Absolutely amazing movie.

This movie is designed to fill plot holes and pander to the star wars fan base with nostalgia. 

Of course as with any blockbuster film churned out by Disney, it has incredible sound design and special effects. But the plot is absolutely atrocious.  

This movie struggles to maintain any relevance for characters suggested to be important in the first movie of this latest trilogy and any form of meaningful character development is neglected. This movie fails to stand alone or support its previous films in any meaningful way and casts a terrible stain on the Star Wars brand. 

I hope that Disney takes careful consideration in how they continue to produce content for the Star Wars franchise so as to maintain its value and rich history.

A movie is supposed to have a vision. The Original Trilogy had a vision. The Prequel Trilogy had a vision. "The Force Awakens" and "The Last Jedi" had a vision, even though they differed from each other. This movie has no vision, it feels like a corporate product, created from fan fictions on the internet. Highlights were really sparse in this. The movie feels empty, I felt nearly no emotions while watching it. It tries so hard to satisfy its audience, that it becomes bland and doesnâ€˜t do anything new or interesting to discuss.
It a very watchable standalone film in the series i guess. but as a trilogy.. its all over the place.

Long time fan and I can except it as the end...and it actually made me care about Rey for once
This is my second time seeing this movie, and it still blows me away. I shall forever love Star Wars and the Skywalker Saga. Everyone needs to watch this movie.

The Rise of Skywalker is definitely a mixed bag. The movie pry's for your nostalgia by playing music from previous films and references to old and new characters. It's nice to reference these things but it is done in a *wink wink* style where jj and Disney take you by the hand and take you to all the things that make a Star Wars film and saying "look at how relatable we are." This film has its moments but it's ultimately a lousy and disrespectful conclusion to a 40 year old franchise...
